# ASCII quotes and apostrophes only

When writing or editing **any** content — files in this repo, Cursor plan documents, issue and PR descriptions and comments, and any other generated text — use **only** ASCII straight quotes and apostrophes:

- **Double quote:** ASCII 0x22 `"` — never Unicode U+201C or U+201D (curly/smart double quotes).
- **Apostrophe / single quote:** ASCII 0x27 `'` — never Unicode U+2018 or U+2019 (curly/smart single quotes).

Curly quotes break search/replace and make later edits fail. Do not use them. This applies to all output (repo files, plans, issues, PRs, comments, docs).

**If a replace fails on content you wrote:** The file may contain curly quotes. Run the normalizer on the **directory that contains it** (e.g. for a repo: `polisher/.venv/bin/python polisher/facts/normalize_ascii_quotes.py <repo-path>`; for Cursor plans: same script with `~/.cursor/plans`). Then retry the replace. Do not work around the mismatch with inline scripts.
